- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Craig interpolation, a logical technique used in automated theorem proving and model checking.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as Craig interpolation is used in various AI applications such as planning and verification.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of the scheme in an interpolating SMT solver.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper may involve algorithmic techniques for computing interpolants.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the practical implications of the proposed scheme for software verification and testing.
